              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13996511071395140585">This book probably marks the emergence of Manu Joseph as a more confident author who decides that certain plotlines are too mainstream, choosing to say the story the way he wants it. This one is darker, more tragic and will perhaps haunt you for a time. In the author&apos;s own words, the worst kind of tragedy is the one that makes you laugh. This one does. As a footnote, may I add that I couldn&apos;t identify the appropriateness of the title even after reading the book. <br/>Strange book.</span>
  <span id="freeText13996511071395140585" style="display:none">This book probably marks the emergence of Manu Joseph as a more confident author who decides that certain plotlines are too mainstream, choosing to say the story the way he wants it. This one is darker, more tragic and will perhaps haunt you for a time. In the author's own words, the worst kind of tragedy is the one that makes you laugh. This one does. As a footnote, may I add that I couldn't identify the appropriateness of the title even after reading the book. <br />Strange book.</span>
