<div id="review_459057971" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/459057971" />
    <a title="Gayatri Makhijani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5851295-gayatri-makhijani"><img alt="Gayatri Makhijani" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/459057971?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gayatri Makhijani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gayatri Makhijani" href="/user/show/5851295-gayatri-makhijani">Gayatri Makhijani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer459057971" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13817139383152898712">You remember some Sundays in, because someone significant has died, and the city you live in, is at a standstill.<br/><br/>You curl up with Manu Joseph&apos;s The Illicit Happiness of Other People, and you cannot stop until the end.<br/><br/>Your heart breaks for Mariamma.<br/><br/>Your heart angers for Philipoise. And the true and tragic nature of life that allows men like him to thrive.<br/><br/>Your heart yearns for Thoma. And, the sad-happy moments of life that make men out of boys.<br/><br/>Your heart saddens for Ousep.<br/><br/>And, your heart leaps for</span>
  <span id="freeText13817139383152898712" style="display:none">You remember some Sundays in, because someone significant has died, and the city you live in, is at a standstill.<br /><br />You curl up with Manu Joseph's The Illicit Happiness of Other People, and you cannot stop until the end.<br /><br />Your heart breaks for Mariamma.<br /><br />Your heart angers for Philipoise. And the true and tragic nature of life that allows men like him to thrive.<br /><br />Your heart yearns for Thoma. And, the sad-happy moments of life that make men out of boys.<br /><br />Your heart saddens for Ousep.<br /><br />And, your heart leaps for Unni. Idiot Unni, confused Unni, clever Unni, extraordinary Unni, Mythili and Unni, Unni…oh Unni...<br /><br />Why did you do what you did?<br /><br />I recommend this book. It is witty, wise and introspective.</span>
